john bennett herrington (born september 14, 1958 in chickasaw nation) is a retired united states naval aviator and former nasa astronaut. in 2002, herrington became the first enrolled member of a native american tribe to fly in space. (william r. pogue was of choctaw ancestry and was a crewman aboard skylab 4 in 1973â€“1974, but he was not an enrolled member of the choctaw.)